-- DuplicateValueBinding (R-DUP-BINDING): a nullary top-level VALUE binding
-- defined twice.  A value binding admits exactly one clause (no argument to
-- discriminate on), so the second definition silently last-wins at eval and
-- miscompiles to runtime garbage; resolve flags it instead.  Multi-clause
-- FUNCTIONS (whose clauses each carry a discriminating pattern) are unaffected.
int = 4
int = 5
main = println int
